  title: 平陽君臣朴錫命等謝賜祿牌箋
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 至仁育物惟務生成厚渥渾身曷勝感激光浮象魏喜溢堪輿伏念臣等猥以庸材幸遭煕運位參廊廟早霑踰分之榮功乏絲毫難免素飧之誚顧荷恩之益腆玆撫己以增慙玆盖伏遇法施祿於羲經稽錫福於禹範謂臣隣常効勞於從事宜人主當優待以養廉遂令斗筲之資咸被丘山之惠謹當矢心圖報銘骨不忘食之飮之載賡歌於飽德悠也久也恒祝壽於齊天
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 平陽君臣朴錫命等謝賜祿牌箋
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 至仁育物。惟務生成。厚渥渾身。曷勝感激。光浮象魏。喜溢堪輿。伏念臣等。猥以庸材。幸遭煕運。位參廊廟。早霑踰分之榮。功乏絲毫。難免素飧之誚。顧荷恩之益腆。玆撫己以增慙。玆盖伏遇法施祿於羲經。稽錫福於禹範。謂臣隣常効勞於從事。宜人主當優待以養廉。遂令斗筲之資。咸被丘山之惠。謹當矢心圖報。銘骨不忘。食之飮之。載賡歌於飽德。悠也久也。恒祝壽於齊天。
korean:
  title: 평양군신 박석명 릉이 녹패의 하사를 사례하는 글
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 지극한 인(仁)이 만물을 기르매 오직 생성(生成)함을 힘쓰고, 두터운 은혜가 몸에 젖으니 감격을 어찌 견디겠습니까. 빛은 대궐에 뜨며 기쁜 것이 천지에 넘칩니다.엎드려 생각하건대 신 등은 외람되이 용렬한 재질로써 다행히 융성한 시대를 만나 벼슬이 묘당(廟堂)에 참여하여 일찍이 분수에 넘치는 영화를 받았으나 공은 터럭만큼도 없으니, 일을 하지 않고 공밥 먹는다는 비방을 면하기 어려운데, 도리어 더욱 두텁게 은혜를 받으니 이에 제 몸을 돌아봄에 부끄러움을 더합니다.이것은 대개 전하께서 녹(祿)을 베푸는 것을 복희씨(伏羲氏)의 주역(周易)에서 본받고, 복을 주는 것은 우(禹)의 홍범(洪範)에 상고하여서 이르시기를, “신하들이 매양 공로가 있었으니 의당 임금이 우대하여서 염치를 기르게 해야 한다.” 하시어 드디어 하찮은 자질로 하여금 구산(丘山) 같은 큰 은혜를 입게 하심을 만난 것입니다. 삼가 마땅히 마음에 맹세하여 갚기를 도모하고 뼈에 새기어 잊지 않으며, 먹이고 마셔 주심을 잊지 않아 곧 덕에 배불렀다는 노래를 부르며, 길고 오래됨은 항상 하늘과 같기로 축수하겠습니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0410_010_0220&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Letter of Gratitude from the Officials of Pyongyang, Including Park Seok-myeong, for the Bestowal of Salary Plaques
  author: Byeon Gye-ryang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The supreme benevolence that nurtures all things aims only at growth and creation. When such generous grace permeates one's very being, how can the heart endure such gratitude? Light spreads across the palace halls, and joy overflows throughout heaven and earth.

    Humbly we consider: we servants, unworthy though we are of meager talent, have by fortune encountered this age of prosperity. Our positions have been raised to the councils of state, and we have early received honors beyond our merit. Yet our accomplishments are but a hair's breadth, and we cannot escape the reproach of eating without working. All the more does this deeper grace bestow upon us shame when we look upon ourselves.

    This comes because Your Majesty models the bestowal of stipends upon the wisdom of Fuxi's Book of Changes, and grants blessings according to Yu the Great's Comprehensive Principles. Thus you declare: "Our ministers have ever labored in their duties; surely the ruler should honor them well and cultivate their integrity." And so even we of humble capacity receive blessings as vast as mountains.

    We solemnly pledge our hearts to requite this kindness and engrave it upon our bones, never to forget. As we partake of sustenance granted us, we sing of souls made full by virtue. For long years to come, we shall ever pray that your life endure eternal as the heavens themselves.
  footnotes:
    - The "salary plaques" (녹패) were official tokens or certificates conferring the privilege of receiving government salaries and stipends.
    - Fuxi (복희씨) and Yu the Great (우) are legendary sage-rulers of ancient China, invoked here as exemplars of virtuous governance.
    - The phrase "eating without working" reflects the Confucian concern that officials should justify their positions through merit and service.
